Abuja – The All Progressive Congress, APC, has approved a zoning formula for the party ahead of its National Convention. The decision was taken during a meeting of the Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) of the APC. Director of Publicity, Salisu Na’inna Dambatta, disclosed this in a statement in Abuja on Wednesday. Below is the zoning arrangement for the party; NORTH-CENTRAL*: Benue, Kogi, Kwara, Nasarawa, Niger and Plateau States SOUTH-SOUTH*: Akwa Ibom, Bayelsa, Cross River, Delta, Edo and Rivers States   SOUTH-EAST*: Abia, Anambra, Ebonyi, Enugu and Imo States NORTH-EAST*: Adamawa, Bauchi, Borno, Gombe, Taraba and Yobe States NORTH -WEST*: Jigawa, Kaduna, Kano, Katsina, Kebbi, Sokoto and Zamfara States Source CONCERTED efforts by Governor Nasir El-Rufai of Kaduna State, to rally his All Progressives Congress, APC, colleagues to save the party appear to be yielding fruit. Party sources say two indicators point to this. At the meeting with APC governors on Tuesday, President Muhammadu Buhari affirmed his choice of Senator… In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has postponed its national convention earlier scheduled for February 26 to March 26, 2022. The decision which was communicated to the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on Monday was signed by the Chairman of the APC Caretaker… In "Top Stories" ......We’ll stick to 2017 distribution of offices .......Ugwuanyi panel meets with party chiefs in Enugu Abuja - Key leaders of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the North have proposed that the next national chairman of the opposition party should come from the South. The proposal is the highlight of… In "Politics"